Daniel Deajir, Chairman of Buruku Local Government Area of Benue State is dead. Deajir, 52, died Thursday evening at a hospital in Makurdi, the state capital. Governor Samuel Ortom confirmed the loss on Friday in a statement by his spokesman, Terver Akase. Ortom said the death was “shocking and devastating.” He described Deajir, who was elected chairman in March 2020, as a gentleman and diligent administrator. Ortom added that the deceased was already making a positive impact in his stewardship. The governor consoled the people of Buruku and Deajir’s family. He further prayed for the repose of departed soul.